            <title>[CASSANDRA-19184] logback-core-1.2.12.jar vulnerability: CVE-2023-6481</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-19184</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-6481&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-6481&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A serialization vulnerability in logback receiver component part of logback version 1.4.13, 1.3.13 and 1.2.12 allows an attacker to mount a Denial-Of-Service attack by sending poisoned data. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</description>
